alerts.title: Coastal Flood Advisory
alerts.description: ...COASTAL FLOODING WILL LIKELY CONTINUE INTO MONDAY... ...AREAS OF DUNE EROSION AND LOCALIZED WASHOVERS POSSIBLE ALONG THE OCEAN BEACHFRONT INTO MONDAY... ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM THIS MORNING TO 1 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... * LOCATIONS...Vulnerable tidal areas of northeastern New Jersey, and vulnerable areas along the north shore of Queens county, and the shores of New York and Bronx counties. * TIDAL DEPARTURE...1 to 1 1/2 feet above astronomical tides above today. * TIMING...Minor coastal flooding expected with the high tides this morning. * COASTAL FLOOD IMPACTS...Inundation of 1 to 2 feet above ground level expected. Some roads and low lying properties will experience shallow flooding. Time of high total tides are approximate to the nearest hour.
